{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.17",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 17 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:1",
      "text": "My breath is corrupt, my days are extinct, the graves are ready for me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:2",
      "text": "Are there not mockers with me? and doth not mine eye continue in their provocation?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:3",
      "text": "Lay down now, put me in a surety with thee; who is he that will strike hands with me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:4",
      "text": "For thou hast hid their heart from understanding: therefore shalt thou not exalt them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:5",
      "text": "He that speaketh flattery to his friends, even the eyes of his children shall fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:6",
      "text": "He hath made me also a byword of the people; and aforetime I was as a tabret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:7",
      "text": "Mine eye also is dim by reason of sorrow, and all my members are as a shadow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:8",
      "text": "Upright men shall be astonied at this, and the innocent shall stir up himself against the hypocrite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:9",
      "text": "The righteous also shall hold on his way, and he that hath clean hands shall be stronger and stronger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:10",
      "text": "But as for you all, do ye return, and come now: for I cannot find one wise man among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:11",
      "text": "My days are past, my purposes are broken off, even the thoughts of my heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:12",
      "text": "They change the night into day: the light is short because of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:13",
      "text": "If I wait, the grave is mine house: I have made my bed in the darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:14",
      "text": "I have said to corruption, Thou art my father: to the worm, Thou art my mother, and my sister.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:15",
      "text": "And where is now my hope? as for my hope, who shall see it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.17.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 17:16",
      "text": "They shall go down to the bars of the pit, when our rest together is in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
